Sentencas: A dense NiO-Fe2O3 (NiFe) pellet has been developed as a potential anode -support for thin-film solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Surface Modification of NiFe Anode for Thin-Film Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: However, preparation of dense NiFe is very challenging.
Titulo: Surface Modification of NiFe Anode for Thin-Film Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Hole-formed NiFe pellets or porous NiFe pellets are frequently formed, which cannot be used as a support (substrate) for thin-film SOFCs.
Titulo: Surface Modification of NiFe Anode for Thin-Film Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Therefore, this hole-formed NiFe support is simply wasted.
Titulo: Surface Modification of NiFe Anode for Thin-Film Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: In this report, we attempt to re-qualify this NiFe support to be a valuable substrate, which can be used for fabricating thin-film SOFCs.
Titulo: Surface Modification of NiFe Anode for Thin-Film Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: By deposition of smaller NiFe particles to cover the hole-formed NiFe support, the surface of this NiFe pellet is modified.
Titulo: Surface Modification of NiFe Anode for Thin-Film Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Large holes on the surface disappear.
Titulo: Surface Modification of NiFe Anode for Thin-Film Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The newly formed NiFe support can be used for fabricating a single cell with La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta as thinfilm electrolyte operated at intermediate temperature.
Titulo: Surface Modification of NiFe Anode for Thin-Film Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Maximum power density generated from this cell is 0.45, 0.86 and 1.28 W cm-2 at 873, 923 and 973 K, respectively.
Titulo: Surface Modification of NiFe Anode for Thin-Film Solid-Oxide Fuel Cell
